deck: The most intelligent 17-year-old on the planet, Tanya Spears has inherited the mantle of Power Girl from Earth-2's Karen Starr. She is a member of Teen Titans.
description:
Origin

Tanya Spears is the daughter of the scientist, Somya Spears. At age 17, Tanya is already a postdoc at the Massachusetts Institute of Technology. She worked at Starr Industries, where she helped Huntress retrieve stolen isotopes so that she and Power Girl could return to Earth-2.

After Power Girl and Huntress used a portal to return to Earth-2, Tanya found she had suddenly gained superhuman abilities much like Power Girl's. It seems that Power Girl passed on her mantel to Tanya through as of yet unknown means of giving the human her powers. Even with her considerable intellect, Tanya is unsure of how she acquired her new powers, but hypothesizes that it was because of her proximity to the portal to Earth-2 when it collapsed.

Since gaining her powers Tanya has joined the Teen Titans and has been an active member ever since.

Creation

Tanya Spears was created by Paul Levitz and first appeared in 2014's World's Finest #23.

Major Story Arcs

Powers & Abilities

Tanya Spears possesses a genius level intellect science.

Following transformation into the new Power Girl, she has displayed superhuman strength, invulnerability, and flight. In addition to these powers Tanya also has the ability to increase her size and although the upper limits as of now are unknown she has shown to be able to grow as tall as an average building.

deck: Leader of the Retaliators of earth-8, American Crusader is a character analog to Captain America.
description:
Native of the universe know as earth 8, American Crusader is the leader of the Retaliators and he represents the spirit of his team: Ready.

When the heroes from several parallels universes crashed in his homeworld, the American Crusader was the first one to stand against them, being cautious about their origins and intentions but he was ready to stop the attack of interdimensional forces upon his world, including the zombie versions of himself and his allies.

Weapons

American Crusader uses a shield capable of expanding itself to protect him and others from any attack or danger.

American Crusader is a homage/doppelganger character based on Captain America. As the Marvel character he also uses a shield as main weapon.
name: American Crusader

deck: Leader of the Future Family from earth-8 and a "Doc" Future exists on Earth-7
description:
Frank Future made a cameo appearence in Final Crisis: Superman Beyond 1. His identity was revealed in The Multiversity 1 as a Mr. Fantastic homage character and the chief of a team analog to the Fantastic Four.

The leader of the Future Family, Frank Future keep their world safe from threats like the destructive Lord Havok and the Extremists. However, it is possible that he is responsible for the origin of Lord Havok, but the circumstances still are unknown.

A parallel version of Frank Future existed in earth-7, know as Doc Future. If earth-8 Frank Future also uses that codename, is unclear but very plausible.
name: Frank Future

deck: Fallen Superman of earth-36 and leader of Justice-9
description:
Optiman was native of earth-36 and one of the analogs of Superman through the multiverse. In his world his role was similar to the last son of Krypton, as the leader and inspiration for the super team Justice-9. He also was recruited by Captain Marvel as member of the Supermen of the Multiverse against Mandrakk. However he was no match to Superdoom, a thought robot from earth-45, who killed him, depiste the help of the other heroes.

However that was not the last time than Optiman would appear. He returned as a gentrified zombie to haunt his former teamates as part of the Gentry attack. Apparentely however, the menace was halted and now Optiman again rest in peace.

As the rest of the natives of earth-36, Optiman is a homage/parody to Bigbang's Ultiman who is indeed a homage/parody to Superman himself.

deck: A detective and friend of Jim Corrigan.
description:
A homicide detective with the 11th Precinct in New York City.

Major Story Arc

Secret Weapon

The Spectre #16

Jim Corrigan calls his old partner Lt. Pete Quarrel to help him out. Pete reluctantly agrees and drives Jim around New York City til they find the body of the criminal Jim shot with a ghost bullet. Pete agrees to help Jim stop The Blood Red Moon Gang, and Pete quickly learns that the Spectre dwells inside his old partner. Pete then goes along with Jim to stop the Blood Red Moon Gang, where he witnesses the Spectre destroy a demon, burn down a lighthouse, and kill the New York branch of the Blood Red Moon.

After seeing this Pete emits to Jim, that he now believes in souls, and heaven and hell.

Every Cop a Criminal

The Spectre #17

Pete Quarrel is investigating 8 drug pushers being murdered in two weeks, then when the latest victim is a Narc, Pete calls on his old partner Jim Corrigan and his alter ego the Spectre. The pair track down the leader of the drug ring, Groschen, a dirty cop and Quarrel's partner before Corrigan. Pete asks Jim to use the Spectre to bring the drug ring down. Jim reluctantly agrees and after the Specter kills Groschen and his thugs in gruesome ways, regrets his desicion and takes his anger out on Corrigan. Quarrel pushes Corrigan and Jim punches Pete and quickly gets shot in the head.

Zombie Transit

The Spectre #18

Pete is there when Jim Corrigan is shot in the head and killed. He is there when Jim's body is taken to the hospital and pronounced dead, and taken to the morgue. Pete is the one who calls Kim Liang and tells her that her boyfriend is dead. Then when Jim becomes a walking corpse, Pete and Kim follow the path of destruction that the walking corpse leaves behind. Pete is there when Jim returns to his apartment, and it is there when The Spectre informs Jim's friends that he and Jim now share a body.
